	* Added new generator PixelChargeSmearer - smears already existing charged diodes
	* PixelCrossTalkGenerator now uses cond db access
	* Removed obsolete charge processes in PixelDigitization
	
2007-03-13 Fredrik Tegenfeldt <fredrik.tegenfeldt@cern.ch>
	* Cond DB access code in place and it works ( calib+special pixels )
	* Added new generator for special pixels map: SpecialPixelGenerator
	  - either reads from db or creates random maps
	* PixelDigitization:
	  - simulates Interval Of Validity (IOV) for generated special pixel maps
	  - accessors to all calib consts
	* New members in configurable for simulated IOV
	* ------- NOTE -------
	this is a intermediate checkin, functional with 12.5.0, should not be tagged
	

2007-02-21 Fredrik Tegenfeldt <fredrik.tegenfeldt@cern.ch>
	* Implemented a configurable PixelDigitization class
	  New file: python/JobOptCfg.py -> contains class inheriting from the
	  automatically generated class in genconf.
	* Cleaned up main PixelDigitization class
	* Added first support for conditions database access
	  NOT YET FULLY IMPLEMENTED...
	* PixelNoisyCellGenerator modified, PixelDiodeNoiseGenerator is now obsolete
	* Tagged as PixelDigitization-00-05-24

2007-01-15 Thijs Cornelissen <thijs.cornelissen@cern.ch>
	* Remove symlinks

2007-01-14 Thijs Cornelissen <thijs.cornelissen@cern.ch>
	* Fix compile error

2007-01-14 David Quarrie <David.Quarrie@cern.ch>
	* Backwards compatible changes for Gaudi v19 compatibility

2006-12-12 Fredrik Tegenfeldt <fredrik.tegenfeldt@cern.ch>
	* PixelDigitization.cxx/h
	  Moved to IAtRndmGenSvc. PixelDigitization now initialises a
	  HepRandomEngine pointer with a given name and seeds.
	* PixelDiodeNoiseGenerator.cxx/h
	  Added HepRandomEngine
	  Modified noise charge = offset + variation (no abs value)
	* PixelNoisyCellGenerator.cxx/h
	  Added HepRandomEngine
	  Modified noise charge = offset + variation (no abs value)
	* PixelSimpleSurfaceChargesGenerator.cxx/h
	  Added HepRandomEngine
	* PixelTimeWalkGenerator.cxx/h
	  Added HepRandomEngine
	* share/PixelDigitization_jobOptions.py
	  added AtRndmGenSvc and seed control
	* cmt/requirements
	  added AthenaKernel
	* tag PixelDigitization-00-05-20
	
2006-11-27 Grant Gorfine <gorfine@cern.ch>
	* PixelDigitization.cxx: Fix to work for Endcap A cosmic
	  geometry.
	
2006-10-09 Fredrik Tegenfeldt <fredrik.tegenfeldt@cern.ch>
	* requirements
	  Fixed checkreq warning
	
2006-07-04 Fredrik Tegenfeldt <fredrik.tegenfeldt@cern.ch>
	* PixelDigitization.cxx/h, PixelDigitization_jobOptions.py:
	  Made TOT parametrization controllable from job obtion file
	  Cleaned up the code and added more comments

2006-06-12 Marian Zdrazil <mzdrazil@lbl.gov>
        * Implemented modifications needed in the Pixel EndCap C Cosmics
          simulation. Remove EndCap A and Barrel modules from the digitization.
          Eventually, we should further modify the code to be able to access
          the conditions database (COOL) via InnerDetector/InDetConditions/Pixel_ConditionsAlgs
          that does not exist yet. So, does not exist the dataset for pixel
          detector in the condDB.    

2006-03-04 Grant Gorfine <gorfine@nikhef.nl>        
	* PixelSimpleSurfaceChargesGenerator, PixelDigitization_jobOptions.py: 
	  Fixed potential division by very small number and wrong step
	  length calculation.
	  Make use of numberOfSteps (as in SCT). G4step is split into
	  sub-steps and then split into sub-charges. Changed default job
	  options properties to reproduce old behaviour (one charge per step). 

